  "text": "In evaluation of the process-oriented training, health professionals described that they did not have adequate time available to pursue the education during working hours. They described that despite decision making heads expressed an interest in the training the health professionals experienced that they did not have reasonable conditions to pursue the course (unpublished data). This points to lack of understanding among heads of organizations that competent health professionals require reasonable conditions to develop good quality in health care [CITATION_1] . Evidence based health care demand possibilities for health professionals to develop their abilities and knowledge during working hours. Heads of health care should not assume that midwives and nurses shall dedicate their free time for professional development.",
